content:
Saw these guys in Cincinnati, OH on February 13th, 2020.  Right before COVID hit.  Awesome show, couldn't have been better.  I took my 6 year old son, and my 9 year old daughter, who are big fans as well.  We still talk about that show, and remember it was the last time we went out and had fun before COVID.  Tarek and Justin acknowledged my kids during and after their show.  Justin gave my son a drum stick and Tarek signed the set list and gave it to my daughter.  Tarek also took pics with them and talked to them for a few minutes.  My kids and I will remember that night for the rest of our lives.

I watched the Live on Display show when was being played live back in October (my kids were at school).  My kids and I watched it later on.  It took us back to that night in February when the world felt so much different and we relived all of the fun things that happened.  We loved everything about the Live on Display show.  The music, the set, lighting, and especially the two great guys  playing the music.  



Also, I would be remiss if I didn't give a big shout out to JJ Wilde who was the supporting act for The Blue Stones that night.  After her show, she sat down and talked to my kids about music, asked them what their interests were, and took pics with them.  I  highly recommend seeing her and her band.  They are fantastic.

Lyrics
[Verse]
Bang my head against the wall
Try to find my stride but I trip and I fall
Losing my attention again
Yeah, I hit the bottom but I'm on the mend

I get up
Take another step, push it to the edge
I get up
Just a little more, I can see the end
I get up
Yeah, you're finished, yeah, you're mine, always win in due time
[Chorus]
You think too much, it's in my head
So, I'm shaking off the rust and
You got no trust, it's in my head
So, I'm shaking off the rust
I think I broke just a little bit
Walked through the fire, made it back again
Lord knows I tried everything I can
Now, I'm shaking off the rust
(I'm shaking off the rust)


[Verse 2]
Bang my head against the wall
Try to hold a smile but I'm sick of it all
Everyone with something to say
Better hold my tongue or I'll make my mistake

[Pre-Chorus]
I get up
Show 'em what I do, show 'em how it's done
I get up
Never turn it down, never gonna run, I learn


[Chorus]
You think too much, it's in my head
So, I'm shaking off the rust and
You got no trust, it's in my head
So, I'm shaking off the rust
I think I broke just a little bit
Walked through the fire, made it back again
Lord knows I tried everything I can
Now, I'm shaking off the rust
(I'm shaking off the rust)


[Bridge]
(I'm, oh)
(I'm shaking off the rust)

[Chorus]
You think too much, it's in my head
So, I'm shaking off the rust and
You got no trust, it's in my head
Now, I'm shaking off the rust
I think I broke just a little bit
Walked through the fire, made it back again
Lord knows I tried everything I can
And I'm shaking off the rust
Yeah, I'm shaking off the rust

content: @Franco Garcia Yup. Although I miss their deep cuts like Criminals and Sawmill, these are the songs that introduced me to this band. Sadly I can't find them anymore neither on YouTube nor on Spotify, it's a good thing I downloaded them off YouTube while they were still available. I feel like some of their newer songs can get a bit cheesy and a bit too clean and sterile for my liking. The potential for greatness is definetly there, but I wish they would bring back the more gritty sound of their earlier music. But hey, that's just my two cents, it's their art and their journey.

content:
Lee Bard 
Yeah, no.  My mother is a wonderful person who I owe a great deal to after how she supported me through crippling depression.  Even when I felt like the world hated me, and I was unlovable, she helped me remember I was worth something.  Despite being a single mom, she put all she could into finding a correct diagnosis for my disability, never giving up until I got the treatment I needed.  She and I are still good friends to this day, after nearly forty years, and she’s still my hero.  Dumping on her once is worth a brief snort of laughter, but it gets old very quickly when people have close bonds with their mothers.

content:
I love this song; the lyrics resonate so deeply, and the music itself gives me chills. When I found this song, I had been utterly out of sync with myself for a long time but was starting to work on that... literally just beginning to get myself back together after [unintentionally] letting myself sink into a depression for nearly three years.
Then the pandemic hits... 
but I had this song, and a few others, that helped me keep my head up. There are many tools a person can utilize to dig themselves up out of whatever dark hole they’re in. This song is one of mine.
Thank you for putting this powerful song into the world; I’d bet I’m not the only one who needed it.

content:
Well, it IS only two people, so I feel like the mass amount of production is warranted, if not expected. To me, songwriting is songwriting, and the instrumentation has evolved to include computers. And while I personally play guitar and prefer live music and recording, I mean...this is DOPE. It's a cool song. Maybe not the most memorable, but in the stylistic-ish genre of newer rock (Highly Suspect, Cleopatrick, etc on 37 Octane, minus all the Linkin Park wannabes, lol) that I am growing to prefer. Even a lot of the hybridization of newer hard rock and hip hop, like say, Fever 333 (RATM for the 21st Century!) is fucking awesome. 

I've come to appreciate simplicity, and a good song is a good song. Your mileage, as always, may vary.

content: This song is amazing, the variation between clean guitar guitar and drive effects really sound great, feels awesome , kinda empowers you. And just discovered of well it sounds with reverbed piano ... reminds me a lot of Bat for lashes' piano, another great band ! No seriously this piano sound so goood ! One day you should try a full 'quieter-slow' version with orchestra, namely strings, just like Kflay did with "Make me fade 'orchestral version'", not same style but I can find some common points between your songs, and I feel your song could also sound great using some piano + cello, especially on the building part ('Lords know I tried everything I can ...'). Anyway thank you for this, loved it

content: I'm starting to think that youtube has a program or algorithm or some type of automated down vote system in place to make absolutely sure that not one video posted on this platform gets only thumb up votes. I understand that this song isn't everybody's cup of tea but I've come across a few videos that (in my humble opinion) couldn't possibly have anything negative said about it (like those 'faith in humanity restored' videos) or get a single down vote...but as sure as the sun will rise in the east, they ALL have a number greater than zero just under the thumb down icon. What I can't figure out is "why would this platform have an automatic down voter for in the first place?" This is a groovin song and for those "people" who clicked the thumb down icon, I just have to ask: if you didn't like the song, why didn't you use your time more efficiently and go straight to clicking on the "get me the hell away from this video" button/tab/icon?

Hace 2 meses mi novia termino conmigo , literalmente sentí que toque fondo , pensé mucho en que hice mal , me rompi en varios pedazos , ya que fui el hombre fiel que le daba todo lo que podía. Pase por infiernos en mi vida y muchos problemas de salud y familiares , pero está canción , justo está canción , me describió en un segundo , así que debería sacarme el polvo y darle con todo. Esta banda la escucho desde que sacaron black holes y la verdad es lo mejor que escuche , siempre identificado , siempre da ánimos , siempre recordar quién eres para seguir adelante. Si vienen a Argentina voy a todos sus shows jajaja

content: I first met you (musically talking) with this song last year. I was travelling by car from Firenze to Perugia the 1st of June. The day before we were all with jumpers on due to winter time ( May had been exceptionally rainy), the day later we came out all with t-shirts (temperatures had risen at last). Summer was there finally. I spent a whole day in Perugia all alone, listening to your songs, walking among people, museums, etc. the sun was shining and beauty was everywhere. On the way driving back home I saw the best sunset I had ever seen in my life on Lake Trasimeno. That's why I will never forget that day. Thank you, I wish you all the success that you deserve, with love 🌹
